{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"da02e15f-ad17-432a-865d-72aebfe094f7","content":"You're on **MSTest 3.8.2 / .NET 9**, so you can use the modern patterns:\n\n### Recommended approach\n\n| Need | Mechanism |\n|---|---|\n| `TestContext` | **Constructor injection** (MSTest v3+) |\n| Sync init | **Constructor** |\n| Async init | **`[TestInitialize]`** with `async Task` |\n\n```csharp\n[TestClass]\npublic class MyTests\n{\n    private readonly TestContext _testContext;\n    private HttpClient _client = null!;\n\n    // Constructor: sync init + TestContext injection\n    public MyTests(TestContext testContext)\n    {\n        _testContext = testContext;\n    }\n\n    // Async init runs before each test\n    [TestInitialize]\n    public async Task InitAsync()\n    {\n        _client = await CreateAuthenticatedClientAsync();\n    }\n\n    [TestMethod]\n    public async Task MyTest()\n    {\n        _testContext.WriteLine(\"Running test...\");\n        var response = await _client.GetAsync(\"/api/data\");\n        Assert.IsTrue(response.IsSuccessStatusCode);\n    }\n\n    [TestCleanup]\n    public void Cleanup() => _client?.Dispose();\n}\n```\n\n**Key points:**\n- **Constructor injection** of `TestContext` replaces the legacy `public TestContext TestContext { get; set; }` static property pattern.\n- Put sync setup in the **constructor**, async setup in **`[TestInitialize]`** — don't use `Task.Run` or `.Result` to force async work into the constructor.\n- For cleanup, use `[TestCleanup]` (supports `async Task` too) or implement `IAsyncDisposable`.","toolRequests":[],"interactionId":"341a07a6-bffb-4dea-8a82-be183a9f33da","reasoningOpaque":"","reasoningText":"They're using MSTest 3.8.2 on .NET 9.0. In modern MSTest (v3+), the recommended approach is:\n\n1. **TestContext injection**: Use constructor injection (`TestContext` as a constructor parameter) rather than the legacy static property pattern.\n2. **Synchronous init**: Use the constructor.\n3. **Asynchronous init**: Use `[TestInitialize]` with an `async Task` method.\n\nLet me also mention that in MSTest 3.x, the `TestContext` property pattern still works, but constructor injection is the modern, recommended way.\n\nKey points:\n- Constructor injection for `TestContext` (MSTest 3.x+)\n\n\n- For cleanup, you can use `[TestCleanup]` or implement `IAsyncDisposable`/`IDisposable` for more control over resource management.","outputTokens":640,"requestId":"A032:AFC07:19529DE:1CB98E4:69FE8F1B"},"id":"3bb41a52-c7ac-410f-9905-dbc0f2a9fb7a","timestamp":"2026-05-09T01:34:32.543Z","parentId":"b093ddc2-f5ac-4ff7-843b-427f5b83270d"}
